# TypeScript Testing Standards

Use the project's testing stack: Vitest (`vitest`), Testing Library (`@testing-library/react`), and `jsdom`.

When changing TypeScript code, ensure tests cover public behavior of updated modules and components.

- Keep tests type-safe and avoid `any` unless explicitly justified.
- Prefer testing exported APIs and component behavior over private internals.
- For bug fixes, add a regression test that fails before the fix.
- Validate both success and error handling paths where applicable.
- Put or update tests in `tests/**/*.test.{ts,tsx}` or `src/**/*.test.{ts,tsx}`.
- For React components, prefer user-centric Testing Library queries over implementation details.
- Reuse shared test setup from `tests/setup.ts` instead of duplicating environment bootstrapping.
